Flavors of the World
Wherever we fly around the globe, we have the enviable job
of tasting and savoring the cuisines of the world. We invite
you to share our discoveries while traveling with us.
Entrees
BARBECUED SIRLOIN OF BEEF
Choice Cubes of Beef Sirloin Braised in a
Hearty Midwestern Barbecue Sauce. Accompanied by
Buttered Shell Noodles Romano and Green Peas with
Kernel Corn and Ripe Olive Bits.
LOIN OF PORK NORMANDE
In the Normandy Region of France,
Slices of Oven Roasted Pork Loin are Served
with a Rich Pan Gravy Flavored By the Natural Drippings of
the Roast and Apple Cider. We garnish this French Specialty with
Apple Wedges and Present it with Home Fried Potatoes and
Green Bean Casserole.
CHICKEN WITH CASHEW NUTS
Called "Yao Goh Gee Ding" in China, this Dish Consists of
Plump Chunks of Chicken Breast Simmered
in a Mellow Soy Flavored Sauce Together with Snow Peas,
Bamboo Shoots, Bean Sprouts, Chinese Mushrooms and
Roasted Cashew Nuts which impart a distinctive flavor.
We Serve it with Oriental Fried Rice.
Salad-
GARDEN SALAD MEDLEY
A delightful combination of Macaroni Rings,
Garden Vegetables and Diced Cheddar Cheese,
Artfully Blended with our Seasoned Dressing.
Dinner Roll
Creamery Butter
The Sweet Course
HARVEY WALLBANGER CAKE
Inspired by the Delightful TWA Cocktail, this Light,
Moist Cake is Enhanced by a Blend of Orange Juice and
Creamy Vanilla Pudding ... Topped with a Smooth Orange,
Whipped Cream and Galliano Glaze.
TWA's freshly brewed Coffee
Tea
Sanka
Milk
Dinner Mint
If you have occasion to travel overseas, either to Europe,
Africa, Hawaii or across the Pacific, may we suggest you
consider the convenience of TW A's Around the World Serv-
ice. From East to West, TWA flies to major world centers.
D-95
92
